HEADWORD: Foot valve
<hw>Foot valve</hw>. <fld>(Mech.)</fld> <def>A suction valve or check
valve at the lower end of a pipe; esp., such a valve in a steam-engine
condenser opening to the air pump.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

